For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT TO CREATE A PATHWAY FOR A GRADUATE OF A
10 FOREIGN MEDICAL SCHOOL TO BE LICENSED IN THIS STATE
11 IF HE OR SHE IS OFFERED FULL-TIME EMPLOYMENT AS A
12 PHYSICIAN FROM A HEALTHCARE PROVIDER; AND FOR OTHER
13 PURPOSES.
14
15
Subtitle
16
17 TO CREATE A PATHWAY FOR A GRADUATE OF A
18 FOREIGN MEDICAL SCHOOL TO BE LICENSED IN
19 THIS STATE IF HE OR SHE IS OFFERED FULL-
20 TIME EMPLOYMENT AS A PHYSICIAN FROM A
21 HEALTHCARE PROVIDER.
22
23 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
24
25 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code § 17-95-202, concerning the definitions used
26 in the Arkansas Medical Practices Act, § 17-95-201 et seq., § 17-95-301 et
27 seq., and § 17-95-401 et seq., is amended to add additional subdivisions to
28 read as follows:
29 (4) "Healthcare provider" means a healthcare professional,
30 healthcare facility, or entity licensed or certified to provide healthcare
31 services in this state as recognized by the Arkansas State Medical Board; and
32 (5) "Medically underserved population" means the same as defined
33 in 42 U.S.C. § 254b, as existing on January 1, 2025.
34
35 SECTION 2. Arkansas Code § 17-95-403(b)(3)(A)(iii), concerning the
36 qualifications for a license to practice medicine in this state, is amended
