As Engrossed: H4/9/25 SB601
1 SECTION 3. Arkansas Code § 17-95-403, concerning the qualifications
2 for a license to practice medicine in this state, is amended to add an
3 additional subsection to read as follows:
4 (c)(1) An applicant who is licensed under subdivision
5 (b)(3)(A)(iii)(c) of this section shall:
6 (A) Maintain his or her employment with the original healthcare
7 provider that operates in this state for at least three (3) consecutive years
8 after licensure;
9 (B) Notify the Arkansas State Medical Board within five (5)
10 business days after any change of employer;
11 (C) Appear personally before the Arkansas State Medical
12 Board together with the sponsoring physician who is licensed by the Arkansas
13 State Medical Board; and
14 (D) Present to the Arkansas State Medical Board
15 information as to what area or department in which he or she will be
16 practicing medicine and who will be his or her sponsoring physician.
17 (2) The license issued under subdivision (b)(3)(A)(iii)(c) of
18 this section shall be a provisional license that authorizes practicing
19 medicine only within the clinical programs approved by the sponsoring
20 physician who is licensed by the Arkansas State Medical Board.
21 (3)(A) The Arkansas State Medical Board shall issue each
22 provisional license under subdivision (b)(3)(A)(iii)(c) of this section for a
23 period of one (1) year.
24 (B) At the end of one (1) year, the provisional license
25 issued under subdivision (b)(3)(A)(iii)(c) of this section shall lapse, and
26 if the physician desires to continue the practice of medicine under the
27 provisional license issued under subdivision (b)(3)(A)(iii)(c) of this
28 section, the physician shall:
29 (i) Submit completed renewal forms to the Arkansas
30 State Medical Board providing information as requested by the Arkansas State
31 Medical Board;
32 (ii) Pay a renewal fee as established by the
33 Arkansas State Medical Board; and
34 (iii) If requested, appear in person before the
35 Arkansas State Medical Board, together with the sponsoring physician.
36 (4) At the end of the second year of practice with a provisional
